{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17609397","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17609397"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:45:20+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:45:20+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16105"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16105","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16105"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.48,0.1,0.14,0.19,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8796"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74150"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8796","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8796"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16105"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59641"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4934"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"8498"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20998"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20999"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74150","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74150"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA histological section of testicular tissue is being examined under light microscopy.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the histological appearance of Leydig cells?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Large polygonal cells with eosinophilic cytoplasm and lipid droplets","Elongated cells with condensed nuclei and prominent acrosomes","Flattened cells with thin cytoplasm and elongated nuclei","Round cells with dark nuclei and scant basophilic cytoplasm","Columnar cells with basal nuclei and clear cytoplasm"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct description is that Leydig cells are \u003Cstrong\u003Elarge polygonal cells with eosinophilic cytoplasm and lipid droplets\u003C/strong\u003E. These cells are found in the interstitial space between seminiferous tubules and are responsible for testosterone production. Their abundant eosinophilic cytoplasm reflects their high content of smooth endoplasmic reticulum, while the lipid droplets store cholesterol for steroid hormone synthesis.\u003C/p\u003E            \u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cul\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EElongated cells with condensed nuclei and prominent acrosomes\u003C/strong\u003E describes developing spermatids\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFlattened cells with thin cytoplasm and elongated nuclei\u003C/strong\u003E describes peritubular myoid cells\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERound cells with dark nuclei and scant basophilic cytoplasm\u003C/strong\u003E describes spermatogonia\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EColumnar cells with basal nuclei and clear cytoplasm\u003C/strong\u003E describes Sertoli cells\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E        \u003C/ul\u003E            \u003Cp\u003ELeydig cells also typically have a large, round nucleus with prominent nucleoli, reflecting their high metabolic activity in hormone production.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Leydig cells are large polygonal cells found in the interstitial space between seminiferous tubules in the testes.","Leydig cells contain abundant eosinophilic cytoplasm and prominent lipid droplets due to their role in testosterone production.","These cells typically have a large, round nucleus with prominent nucleoli."],"references":["Aladamat N, Tadi P. Histology, Leydig Cells. [Updated 2022 Nov 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK556007/","Rebourcet D, O\u0027Shaughnessy PJ, Monteiro A, Milne L, Cruickshanks L, Jeffrey N, Guillou F, Freeman TC, Mitchell RT, Smith LB. Sertoli cells maintain Leydig cell number and peritubular myoid cell activity in the adult mouse testis. PLoS One. 2014 Aug 21;9(8):e105687. doi: 10.1371/journal.pone.0105687. PMID: 25144714; PMCID: PMC4140823.","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59641"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16105"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59641","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/59641"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-24T21:43:43+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-24T21:43:53+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8796"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74150"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id